---
description: Code organization & implementation patterns (repo-wide)
alwaysApply: false
---

- Prefer reusable utilities over inline logic once used twice.
- If you’re unsure about intent/spec, stop and ask the user. Don’t guess.
- Prefer minimal, targeted changes; fix root causes.
- Avoid redundant code: reuse existing helpers; consolidate similar logic.
- Keep one primary domain concern per file; keep integration boundaries crisp.
- Prefer `unknown` + narrowing; avoid `any` and avoid non-null assertions (`!`) at boundaries.
- Keep imports at the top; avoid surprise re-exports
- Before adding a new package or library, check current docs + examples; don’t invent APIs.